Sheet 1: Unit Test Information
1.0a






















Nexteer EPS Unit Test Tool






Rev:2.7d












Name of Tester: Spoorti Mali
Source files to be added to the .pjt file Must include path from 'Source Code Directory' setting on the Unit Test Tool Options dialog Include Files:

Code File(s) Under Test: I2cNxtr.c



Code File(s) Version: 2



Module Design Document: I2cNxtr_MDD.docx



Module Design Document Version: 5



Data Dictionary Version: 1



Unit Test Plan Version: 2



Optimization Level: Level 2



Compiler (CodeGen) Version: TMS470_4.9.5



Model Type: Excel Macro



Model Version: Nexteer EPS Unit Test Tool 2.7d/EPS Library 1.30



Total FLASH Used (Bytes): 550



Total RAM Used (Bytes): 12



Total CALS Used (Bytes): 0



Special Test Requirements:




Test Date: 07-25-2014



Comments: 1)The map file"CBD_Sandbox_dbg.map" is embedded for reference.
2) 100% coverage can not achieved for "I2c_Send" and "I2c_SetRecv"function because the condition "While (BitwiseAND(I2cRegPtr_Cnt_T_str.STR, I2C_TX_INT) = 0)" can not be satified as it goes into infinite loop.
3)"I2cNxtr_I2cTransfer_Cnt_M_str_DataPtr_Cnt_u08_add", "DataPtr_Cnt_T_u08_add" and "I2cNxtr_I2cTransfer_Cnt_M_str.DataPtr_Cnt1_u08" temp variables are newly added for testing address in "I2c_Send" and "I2c_SetRecv"functions.
4)In "I2c_Send" and "I2c_SetRecv" function extra code is added in VBA to replicate the functionality of source code and TESSY.
5) The range of "Length_Cnt_T_u32" and " I2cNxtr_I2cTransfer_Cnt_M_str.Length_Cnt_u32" is 0 to 4294967295 but is considered to be 0 to 255 for testing purpose to resrtict the array size of parameter "DataPtr_Cnt_T_u08" and structure variable I2cNxtr_I2cTransfer_Cnt_M_str.DataPtr_Cnt_u08 upto 256 in the fuctions "I2c_Send" and "I2c_SetRecv".
6) In Tessy the target for I2cNxtr_I2cTransfer_Cnt_M_str.DataPtr_Cnt_u08 is created with a different name as "tgt_DataPtr_Cnt1_u08" for testing purpose in the functions " I2cSend" and "I2cSetRcv"
7) In the function"I2cSend" the target "tgt_DataPtr_Cnt1_u08" and the values of the this particular target are ignored for the vectors "TS1.2,TS2.1,TS2.3,TS2.6,TS2.8,TS2.10,TS2.12,TS2.14,TS2.16,TS2.17,TS3.2" as the target names do not match.
8)In the function"I2cSetRcv" the target "tgt_DataPtr_Cnt1_u08" and the values of the this particular target are ignored for all the vectors as they are being verified manually.
9) The output value for the functions"I2c_SetFunctional", "I2c_SetBit", "I2c_EnableNotification", "I2c_DisableNotification", "I2c_GetIntVect", "I2c_SetStatus" is going beyond mentioned range in MDD which will not have any functional impact and will be resolved as continuous improvement.
10) The range for the parameter "Baud_Hz_T_u32" in the function"I2c_SetBaudrate" is considered to be 100000 to 400000 for testing purpose.
